<item>
            <title>[LU-19896] kernel update [RHEL 8.10 4.18.0-553.109.1.el8_10]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19896</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es) for kernel 4.18.0-553.105.1.el8_10:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: smc: Use __sk_dst_get() and dst_dev_rcu() in smc_clc_prfx_match() (CVE-2025-40168)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Linux kernel Bluetooth: Denial of Service due to use-after-free in connection handling (CVE-2023-53762)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Linux kernel: Out-of-bounds write in fbdev can lead to privilege escalation, information disclosure, or denial of service. (CVE-2025-40304)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---8/x86_64/RHSA-2026:2720&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---8/x86_64/RHSA-2026:2720&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es) for kernel 4.18.0-553.109.1.el8_10:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Linux kernel: Denial of Service due to a deadlock in hugetlb folio migration (CVE-2026-23097)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---8/x86_64/RHSA-2026:3464&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---8/x86_64/RHSA-2026:3464&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
